"title": "5853: experience, of life",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5853: experience, of life",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Experience of life comes with increasing age and through observation, reflection and the application of lessons learned. Experience in a craft or profession comes through training and practice.</p>\n<h2>Experience associated with advancing years</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:12\">JOB 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:6-Job32:7\">JOB 32:6–32:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:6-1Kgs12:7\">1KI 12:6–12:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:6-2Chr10:7\">2CH 10:6–10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:25\">PSA 37:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:1-Prov4:4\">PRO 4:1–4:4</a></p>\n<h2>Dissatisfaction with life's experiences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:11\">ECC 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:11\">ECC 3:11</a> <em>People are made for eternity and cannot be fully satisfied with the things of this world</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:13-Eccl1:17\">ECC 1:13–1:17</a> <em>application to study</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:1-Eccl2:3\">ECC 2:1–2:3</a> <em>devotion to pleasure</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:4-Eccl2:6\">ECC 2:4–2:6</a> <em>pursuit of great projects</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:7-Eccl2:8\">ECC 2:7–2:8</a> <em>a life of materialism</em><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:24-Eccl2:26\">ECC 2:24–2:26</a></strong> <em>Human experiences find fulfilment only in relation to God.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:12-Eccl3:14\">ECC 3:12–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:13-Eccl12:14\">ECC 12:13–12:14</a></p>\n<h2>Learning from life's experiences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:32\">PRO 24:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:8-Job4:9\">JOB 4:8–4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:3\">JOB 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:43\">PSA 107:43</a></p>\n<h3>Sympathy resulting from personal experience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:9\">EXO 23:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21\">EXO 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:15\">DEU 15:12–15:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3-2Cor1:4\">2CO 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:32-Heb10:34\">HEB 10:32–10:34</a></p>\n<h3>Growing through experiences</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:3-Rom5:4\">ROM 5:3–5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:8\">HEB 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:2-Jas1:4\">JAS 1:2–1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Learning from everyday experiences</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:32\">MAT 24:32</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:28\">MRK 13:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:2-Matt16:3\">MAT 16:2–16:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:54-Luke12:55\">LUK 12:54–12:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:28-Matt6:31\">MAT 6:28–6:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:27-Luke12:29\">LUK 12:27–12:29</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ shared human experience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17-Heb2:18\">HEB 2:17–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8\">PHP 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Experience in a craft or profession</h2>\n<h3>Skilled craftsmen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:7\">2CH 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:13-2Chr2:14\">2CH 2:13–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:13-1Kgs7:14\">1KI 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:1-Exod36:2\">EXO 36:1–36:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:15-1Chr22:16\">1CH 22:15–22:16</a></p>\n<h3>Experienced soldiers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:12-2Chr17:13\">2CH 17:12–17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:33\">1SA 17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:8\">2SA 17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:33\">1CH 12:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:7-Song3:8\">SNG 3:7–3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Other competent people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:2\">1SA 12:2</a> <em>Samuel's experience in leadership</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:13\">EST 1:13</a> <em>Xerxes consults experts in law and justice</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:4\">MAT 2:4</a> <em>Herod consults teachers of the law</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:2-Acts18:3\">ACT 18:2–18:3</a> <em>Paul and Aquila were experienced tent makers.</em></p>",
